                    "description": "R&D on RF and electronic systems for LEO satellites and ground applications. System engineering support for payload and sub-system development.\n\n\u0095 Technical responsible, leading a team of 5 engineers, for the development of a satellite transceiver: from requirement definition to system verification and flight qualification. \n\u0095 Software Defined Radios: digital modulation / demodulation performed on general purpose computers or custom hardware. Experience with ECSS / CCSDS standards implementation.\n Design support for RF payload development.\n\u0095 RF hardware design and test of satellite and ground-based transceivers with RF output power between 1 and 100 W.\n\u0095 C++ / Java / Python programming for data handling hardware control software. Implementation of a distributed ground station control and data distribution software capable of handling multiple missions and ground stations at the same time.\n\u0095 Development of a flexible and modular line of solar panels for satellites ranging from 1 to 25 kg: design for manufacturing re-using commercial technologies and processes. Electronic design, project coordination and relations with customers. \n\u0095 Managed the development of a modular power system for small satellites with a team of 4 people. Experience with Prince2 methodology.\n\u0095 Practical experience in integration / on-ground and in-flight testing / debugging on several missions. Systems engineering support for platform and payload design.",
